QuestFlags\par
This flag field defines more specifically the type of quest it is. Aside from the daily flag and sharable flag, this field is used just for grouping purposes and NOT for any other quest requirements. The quest requirements are calculated from non-zero values in other quest template fields. Also, while some of these flags are known, others have yet an unknown purpose and the comments below is simply guesswork on them.\par
At the moment (rev 6055), the core does not actually handle these flags any differently (again, except for the daily flag and the sharable flag).\par
Bit\tab  Name\tab  Comments\par
0\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_NONE\tab  No flags, so no groups assigned to this quest.\par
1\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_STAY_ALIVE\tab  If the player dies, the quest is failed. (?)\par
2\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_EVENT\tab  Escort quests or any other event-driven quests. If player in party, all players that can accept this quest will receive confirmation box to accept quest.\par
4\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_EXPLORATION\tab  Involves the activation of an areatrigger.\par
8\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_SHARABLE\tab  Allows the quest to be shared with other players.\par
16\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_NONE2\tab  Unknown at this time and not used.\par
32\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_EPIC\tab  Epic class quests (hunter) (??)\par
64\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_RAID\tab  Raid or similiar player group needed for quest.\par
128\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_TBC\tab  Added with or after TBC.\par
256\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_UNK2\tab  Quest needs extra non-objective items dropped (eg. ReqSourceID fields) (?)\par
512\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_HIDDEN_REWARDS\tab  Item and monetary rewards are hidden in the initial quest details page and in the quest log but will appear once ready to be rewarded.\par
1024\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_UNK4\tab  Unknown at this time.\par
2048\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_TBC_RACES\tab  Blood elf/draenei starting zone quests.\par
4096\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_DAILY\tab  Daily repeatable quests (only flag that the core applies specific behavior for)\par
8192\tab  QUEST_FLAGS_UNK5\tab  Grizzly Hills PvP daily? Puts PvP-tag on? No idea.)\par
Like all flag based fields, QuestFlags can be added for the different types of quest.\par
SpecialFlags\par
This field is a bitmask and controls only two extra requirements and has only 4 possible values.\par
0: No extra requirements\par
1: Makes the quest repeatable.\par
2: Makes the quest only completable by some external event (an entry in areatrigger_involvedrelation, spell effect quest complete or an entry in spell_scripts with command 7 as some examples)\par
3: Both repeatable and completable only through an external event\par
