Amount of required items\par
ReqSourceID\par
Item ID that is needed indirectly by the quest. For example, the quests asks for item X but the only way to get item X is by activating item Y; however, item Y is also a quest item. Therefore you set item Y's ID in this field. This requirement will not appear in the quest text, it is just for the core to know when to drop a quest item that isn't in the ReqItemID field but is still needed by the quest.\par
ReqSourceCount\par
The maximum number of copies of the item in ReqSourceID that can be picked up (and dropped by the core).\par
ReqCreatureOrGOId\par
Value > 0: required creature_template ID the player needs to kill/cast on in order to complete the quest.\par
Value < 0: required gameobject_template ID the player needs to cast on in order to complete the quest.\par
If ReqSpellCast is != 0, the objective is to cast on target, else kill.\par
NOTE: If ReqSpellCast is != 0 and the spell has effects Send Event or Quest Complete, this field may be left empty.\par
ReqCreatureOrGOCount\par
The number of times the creature or gameobject must be killed or casted upon.\par
ReqSpellCast\par
Spell ID of Spell that needs to be cast in order to fulfill a quest objective. A spell normally needs a target which is ReqCreatureOrGOId\par
And for spells with "SpellEffect with ImpliciteTargetA-B == 38" check table Spell_script_target\par
NOTE: If the spell has spell effects Send Event or Quest Complete, it can be entered here WITHOUT the need for a target and count.\par
